ss various decomposition stages, particularly advanced decay classes, along with moderate gap disturbance, promotes the conservation of wood-inhabiting microbial diversity in forest ecosystems. Our study provides indepth insights into the positive effects of forest disturbances, which are essential for informing sustainable forest management practices and preserving ecosystem health.
